{"word":"καῦμα","slug":"καῦμα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>καῦμα</b></el> <el>(καῦμα, ατος, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:καίω'><el>καίω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>burning heat</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> of the sun, <el>καύματος</el> <i>in the sun-heat</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>καῦμ' ἔθαλπε</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>fever-heat</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—<a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of love, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}